{
  "stem": "18307.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 124.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they came up with an idea that they're going to-- they had a-- where they used to keep potatoes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like a cellar in the-- in the ground.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said if they would move all these potatoes from one side to the other and put some boards up and then put the potatoes back on the boards, so even if they burned the farm, we would not die because we were underground.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when we went there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- the boys, my two brothers, and my father, Yaski himself, they moved all these potatoes to one side and they put boards and they put the potatoes and they made a little closing door like you could crawl in and then you-- they-- it's like a little drawer with potatoes and they just put it on top.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So if somebody comes in and looks at potatoes, it's potatoes all over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the floors were cement and we laid in the cold on the cement.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember my mother-- my mother was-- she didn't-- she was cold and-- but this is how we slept on nights.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "During the day, we would go out to the barn, but at night we laid there under those potatoes and we heard the bombings.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We already heard the shots and we knew that the war was coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the closer the bombings came, the happier we got.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one day, we were in the barn on top, like under the-- under the roof like a crawl space and we saw these soldiers riding up on horses with bayonets.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't know what in the world was going on because we never thought that we would ever be free again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The front was-- was right there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
